OL,3,CQueen's had Epstein victims 'in mind'
OL,4,Cin message to sexual abuse survivors
OL,6,FThose in the room at the time are
OL,7,Funderstood to have exchanged glances
OL,8,Fas the Queen spoke, according to one
OL,9,Fof the attendees with whom ITV News
OL,10,Fspoke today.
OL,12,FThe Queen was wearing a badge given to
OL,13,Fher by Gisele Pelicot, who bravely
OL,14,Fwaived her right to anonymity to
OL,15,Fprosecute her husband, who was among
OL,16,F51 men convicted of raping and
OL,17,Fassaulting her at her home in France.
OL,19,FThe message on the badge read: "Shame
OL,20,FMust Change Sides".
